text: Why do I always forget how terrible @UPS is? This is the last time I use them. I will never order an iPhone and have it delivered *EVER* again. The delivery experience has been a complete shit show.
@elliottp That certainly not the impression we want to leave you with. Please let us know if there's anything you'd like my team and I to look into for you. ^JG https://t.co/wKJHDXWGRQ

@UPSHelp You need to fix your policy and allow deliveries, for people that live in apt buildings, to be signed for by the folks in the management office. Plus, it's outrageous that you can't alter delivery options until after a delivery attempt has been made.
@elliottp Our free self service option called MyChoice provides you the option to request we leave packages in the management office.  ^JG https://t.co/wKJHDXWGRQ

@UPSHelp You need to do a better job of making that option clear. I did not see it. I could only find the option where you charged me $5 to "redirect" my delivery to a UPS store near my house. While that sounded worth it - the service there was terrible. #ShitShow

@elliottp U can modify Ur preferences by logging in to UPS MYCHOICE. Once you have logged in, click on your name (right upper corner) > Preference> Edit (under the ups mychoice tab) > Scroll down to 'delivery options' > Click on driver instructions> Under 'location for packages delivery'
